text: Maple Plain Library is a public library in Maple Plain, Minnesota. It opened in 1922. The current building opened in 1973. The library has a meeting room and . Their collection holds Spanish materials in their language collection. This library serves Loretto, Minnetrista, Orono, and Greenfield. == History == The library was in an old post office building in 1922. It was moved to the old State Bank building in 1964. == References == Category:Pages using gadget WikiMiniAtlas Category:Libraries in Hennepin County Library Category:Education in the United States Category:1922 establishments in the United States Category:Pages with unreviewed translations
